{
  "text": "On the other hand, by the discreteness of the eigenvalues [CITATION_1] , we know that all the eigenvalues are excluded some open sets. For this, Li et al. [CITATION_2] proposed some exclusion sets, which exclude open sets respectively from the Gersgorin eigenvalue inclusion set in [CITATION_3] and the Brauer-type eigenvalue inclusion set in [CITATION_4] as follows: [CITATION_5] ) Let A be a complex tensor of order m and dimension n ≥ . Then, all eigenvalues of A are located in the union of the following sets:",
